avdta.dta

Class DTAImportFromVISTA

  • java.lang.Object
    • avdta.dta.DTAImportFromVISTA

  • public class DTAImportFromVISTA
extends java.lang.Object
    This class allows the import of an assignment from VISTA, using the vehicle_path and vehicle_path_time tables from VISTA. To import demand, see DemandImportFromVISTA.

      • DTAImportFromVISTA

        public DTAImportFromVISTA(DTAProject project,
                          java.io.File vehicle_path,
                          java.io.File vehicle_path_time)
                   throws java.io.IOException
        Constructs the DTAImportFromVISTA with the specified project, vehicle_path, and vehicle_path_time table from VISTA. This method takes the VISTA assignment and creates a corresponding assignment for the specified project. Note that vehicle and link ids must match. Importing the network and demand from VISTA will result in matching ids. Also note that new path ids may not match VISTA path ids. However, they will be unique, and corrected for each vehicle.
        Parameters:
        project - the project
        vehicle_path - the file containing the VISTA vehicle_path table
        vehicle_path_time - the file containing the VISTA vehicle_path_time table
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if a file cannot be accessed
